<title>Shop</title>
<h1>Market Place</h1>



<div class="modal fade" id="exampleModalLong" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLongTitle"
    aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog " role="document">
        <div id="modalShopList" class="modal-body" hidden>
            <div class="modal-content">

                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">
                    Close
                </button>

                <ol id="equipmentList"></ol>

                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">
                    Close
                </button>

            </div>

            <script>
                function myFunction() {
                    document.getElementById("modalShopList").removeAttribute("hidden");
                }
                function closeFunction() {
                    document.getElementById("modalShopList").setAttribute("hidden");
                } 
            </script>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>



<div class="marketContainer">


    <div>
        <form hidden class="form" id="equipmentForm">
            <input type="text" id="equipmentInput" placeholder="equipment-name" />
            <input type="submit" id="spellSubmit" onclick="spellSearch()" />
        </form>

      
        <div class="card ">
            <div class="card-header">
                Name: <b> <span id="itemName"></span> </b>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="card-text">
                    <b>Price: </b><span id="itemPrice"></span>
                    <br>
                <p><b>Weight: </b><span id="itemWeight"></span></p>
                </p>
                <b>
                    <span class="card-title">
                        description 1:
                    </span></b>
                <span id="description1"></span><br>
                <b>description 2: </b></br><span id="description2"></span><br>
                <b>description 3:</b> <span id="description3"></span></br>

                <button onclick="myFunction()" type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-toggle="modal"
                    data-target="#exampleModalLong">
                    shop List
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class="card-footer text-muted">

            </div>
        </div>
    


    </div>
</div>


<h1>Conditions</h1>

<div class="conditions">
    <div class="deathThrows">
        <b> Death Saving Throw</b>:<br />
        roll a flat d20 no modifier, three rolls above 10 stabilizes, three
        rolls under 10 you die, roll a 1 counts as 2 fails, roll 20
        automatically alive with 1 hp, damage past 0 that equals your full
        health auto death, party member can administer first aid to stabilize
        must roll DC 10 or hirer Wisdom / Medicine check + modifier, if
        stabilized you remain at 0 hp and stay unconscious but no longer need
        to roll death saving throws
    </div>
    <div class="food">
        <b> Food </b>:<br />
        Can survive with out food for 3 days + Con Mod, beyond that you become
        "exhausted"
    </div>
    <div class="water">
        <b> Water</b>:<br />
        1 - 2 gallons per day depending on heat, after that must make DC 15
        Con saving throw, or become increasingly "exhausted" per day with out
        water
    </div>
    <div class="falling">
        <b>Falling</b>: <br />1d6 bludgeoning damager per 10ft max 20d6, lands
        prone
    </div>
    <div class="suffocating">
        <b>Suffocating</b>: <br />can hold breath for 1min + Con mod past that
        can survive rounds equal to con mod before dying flat out
    </div>

    <div class="blinded">
        <b>Blinded</b> <br />attacks on creature have advantage, blinded has
        disadvantage, automatically fail ability checks that require sight
    </div>
    <div class="charmed">
        <b>Charmed</b><br />can't target the charmer with attacks, ability's
        or spells, charmer has advantage against charmed person
    </div>
    <div class="deafened">
        <b>Deafened</b><br />fails any check that requires hearing
    </div>
    <div class="frightened">
        <b>Frightened</b><br />has disadvantage on all checks and attacks if
        they can see the source of fear, also can not move closer to fear
        source
    </div>
    <div class="grappled"><b>Grappled</b> <br />stuck in place</div>
    <div class="incapacitated">
        <b>Incapacitated</b><br />
        can't take actions or reactions
    </div>
    <div class="invisibl">
        <b>Invisible</b><br />
        impossible to see without magic aid, considered heavily obscured, can
        still be heard attacks while invisible have advantage and attacks
        against an invisible target have disadvantage
    </div>
    <div class="paralyzed">
        <b>Paralyzed</b><br />
        incapacitated can't move or speak automatically fails STR and DEX
        saving throws attacking paralyzed target have advantage, attack hits
        are automatically CRITS if within 5 feet
    </div>
    <div class="petrified">
        <b>Petrified</b><br />
        creature and NON-magical items it has on person turn to stone, Weight
        is multiplied by 10, stops aging, creature in incapacitated unaware of
        surroundings, attacks against creature have advantage, auto fail STR
        and DEX saving throws, has resistance to all damage (half damage),
        immune to poison, and disease, if already poisoned or diseased they
        are paused, not cured
    </div>
    <div class="poisoned">
        <b>Poisoned</b> <br />has disadvantage on attacks and ability checks
    </div>
    <div class="prone">
        <b>Prone</b> <br />can only crawl, until standing up, has disadvantage
        on attacks, attacks to prone target with-in 5 ft have advantage, if
        more than five feet away the attacker has disadvantage
    </div>
    <div class="restrained">
        <b>Restrained</b><br />
        speed becomes 0, disadvantage to DEX saving throw, attacks v
        restrained creature have advantage and attacks from the restrained
        creature have disadvantage
    </div>
    <div class="stunned">
        <b>Stunned</b> <br />becomes incapacitated, faltered speech, auto fail
        STR and DEX saving throws, attacks against creature have advantage
    </div>
    <div class="unconscious">
        <b>Unconscious</b> <br />incapacitated, can't move, speak and is
        unaware of surroundings, immediately drops what ever it is holding and
        falls prone, auto fail STR and DEX saving throw, attack rolls against
        creature have advantage, if hit from creature with in 5 ft it is auto
        crit
    </div>
</div>
